01:41:33,880 --> 01:41:37,440
 So, and then we, we mentioned EPI as an initiative.

948
01:41:37,440 --> 01:41:41,600
 We know in Bizum, in, in Spain that has built on top of that.

949
01:41:42,640 --> 01:41:55,680
 But in order that everybody can use it, you need to make sure that your standard is accepted or implemented at with all merchants across Europe, because otherwise, somebody that wants to pay, the merchant needs to accept it.

950
01:41:55,680 --> 01:42:01,260
 And that's actually still lacking in the whole instant payments environment.

951
01:42:01,260 --> 01:42:09,480
 So, the digital euro would build the standard, a standard, it will be implemented if everything goes on.

952
01:42:10,140 --> 01:42:13,860
 And then, what we say, it's an open standard which could be reused.

953
01:42:13,860 --> 01:42:25,960
 Actually, we think it will help instant payment-based solutions, including those by the TPPs, because they don't need to convince a merchant to implement their standard, because that standard's already there.

954
01:42:25,960 --> 01:42:33,880
 And let's be honest, if I talk about standard, it's a QR code or an alias, which is non-competitive.

955
01:42:33,880 --> 01:42:38,360
 I mean, it's not that somebody says, oh, my QR code is more beautiful than the other QR code.

956
01:42:38,460 --> 01:42:41,840
 I mean, nobody cares, but it's about the value of the transactions.

957
01:42:41,840 --> 01:42:51,120
 So, on that side, we believe the digital euro would actually enable the instant payments more with all the players there.

958
01:42:51,120 --> 01:42:58,020
 The other point is, is that TPPs could also work on the platform for digital euro.

959
01:42:58,300 --> 01:43:08,860
 So, there you would have a platform that's, that's across the whole of Europe and you as a TPP could also build and innovate as you do on the instant payments.

960
01:43:08,860 --> 01:43:15,680
 And since it's both, as we said before, it's an instant settlement, the logic is the same.

961
01:43:15,680 --> 01:43:18,980
 So, only the coin that you transport is differently.

962
01:43:18,980 --> 01:43:20,480
 Thank you.

963
01:43:20,480 --> 01:43:22,360
 We could take it over later with a bit of technical.

964
01:43:22,360 --> 01:43:22,660
 Okay.

965
01:43:22,660 --> 01:43:23,560
 Yeah, right.

966
01:43:23,560 --> 01:43:26,120
 I've seen many more hands raised.

967
01:43:26,120 --> 01:43:27,180
 So, who was the first?

968
01:43:27,180 --> 01:43:27,960
 Yeah, please.

969
01:43:28,520 --> 01:43:34,560
 Thank you very much and thank you to the Croatian National Bank for having us and having this discussion.

970
01:43:34,560 --> 01:43:44,680
 I wanted to address a point that Tamara mentioned about really bringing this into the open and meeting the people who are involved in the digital euro.

971
01:43:44,680 --> 01:43:53,740
 And this idea that, well, has this project been undertaken very quickly in the dark and is that actually an issue?

972
01:43:53,740 --> 01:44:08,220
 And on the other hand, one might say that maybe it needs to be done in the dark to protect us from lobbying efforts by incumbent business models as well.

973
01:44:08,220 --> 01:44:13,920
 So, I think there's a tension here that's really interesting and I'd like to ask you to explore this tension a bit.

974
01:44:14,460 --> 01:44:18,100
 But in the context of what I think are two big elephants in the room, right?

975
01:44:18,100 --> 01:44:41,400
 One of them is the instant payments, which follows up on Cosman's point, which is that maybe if we – do we see this as a responsibility of the ECB to facilitate some kind of instant settlement mechanism in the digital world, a digital cash that does that?

976
01:44:41,400 --> 01:44:43,660
 That's one of these contexts.

977
01:44:43,660 --> 01:44:45,040
 That's one question in this context.

978
01:44:45,040 --> 01:44:56,700
 And the other aspect is, in the context of privacy, it seems like we're talking about Monero, as it was just mentioned, as one extreme, completely in the dark, no regulation at all.

979
01:44:56,700 --> 01:45:05,380
 But on the other hand, no one mentioned the Financial Action Task Force travel rule, which seems to be the, you know, a big elephant in this room, which is the other extreme.

980
01:45:05,380 --> 01:45:11,760
 Everything is completely transparent and all the transparency is just determined ex post by whoever is in power.

981
01:45:11,760 --> 01:45:21,300
 So, have you considered that there are projects like BIS Project Torbillon by the BIS Swiss Center that actually have one party who is anonymous and one party who is not?

982
01:45:21,840 --> 01:45:25,280
 And other kinds of approaches like this do this problem.

983
01:45:25,280 --> 01:45:25,600
 Thanks.

984
01:45:25,600 --> 01:45:27,820
 Thank you.

985
01:45:27,820 --> 01:45:29,700
 I think that all the questions are for you.

986
01:45:29,700 --> 01:45:30,880
 Sorry for that.

987
01:45:30,880 --> 01:45:33,900
 I need to recollect.

988
01:45:33,900 --> 01:45:35,120
 What was the first question again?

989
01:45:35,560 --> 01:45:38,100
 So, the first one is the instant settlement responsibility.

990
01:45:38,100 --> 01:45:39,300
 Yeah.

991
01:45:39,300 --> 01:45:42,400
 But I'm a bit puzzled there.

992
01:45:42,400 --> 01:45:55,920
 So, there is the ECB already has a system, which is called TIPS, so where instant settlement can take place, which is, so that's already there.

993
01:45:56,400 --> 01:46:03,940
 And as we say, we, yeah, we are committed to that, so I don't fully understand.

994
01:46:03,940 --> 01:46:19,520
 And then, of course, there is the settlement of digital euro, which will also be an instant settlement, but it's different things that you settle, because in one, you settle central bank money, digital euro, and in the other, you settle commercial bank money, actually.

995
01:46:20,840 --> 01:46:33,820
 In my context, I mean, the reliance of merchants on credit provision from their networks and these card payment networks, is this actually a problem that you see?

996
01:46:33,820 --> 01:46:39,440
 Merchants that get credit from card schemes?

997
01:46:39,440 --> 01:46:42,300
 Sorry, I don't understand the question.

998
01:46:42,300 --> 01:46:43,320
 You should take it off.

999
01:46:43,320 --> 01:46:45,860
 We will have a break, so you can...

1000
01:46:45,860 --> 01:46:47,040
 Sorry, I don't understand.

1001
01:46:47,040 --> 01:46:49,300
 Just point that one.

1002
01:46:50,840 --> 01:46:53,900
 Sanja, Sanja had a long question.

1003
01:46:53,900 --> 01:46:55,060
 Thank you.

1004
01:46:55,060 --> 01:46:57,660
 Sanja Tomidzic from the Croatia National Bank.

1005
01:46:57,660 --> 01:47:03,240
 Well, actually, I'm also going to address the question to Ms. Whitlocks, unfortunately.

1006
01:47:03,240 --> 01:47:12,700
 Not the other panelists, but all the panelists today are talking about the digital euro project and having in mind and talking about the retail digital euro.

1007
01:47:13,180 --> 01:47:23,960
 And I can, let's say, completely understand the narrative behind the digital euro and especially coming from the international and European relations area.

1008
01:47:25,400 --> 01:47:34,720
 Within this time of the rising geopolitical fragmentation, the strategic autonomy argument seems to me very appealing.

1009
01:47:34,720 --> 01:47:43,440
 And, you know, to have a solution that will work, even if the other solutions or infrastructure spill, is very important.

1010
01:47:43,440 --> 01:47:49,500
 So I definitely can subscribe to this way of payment.

1011
01:47:49,500 --> 01:48:01,080
 But on the other hand, I think that in a steady state, let's say, situation, the wholesale digital euro might be even more important.

1012
01:48:01,220 --> 01:48:14,220
 And especially since it can also boost some other European European Union projects, like the Capital Markets Union, for instance, and not to mention that it could also strengthen the international role of the euro.

1013
01:48:14,220 --> 01:48:21,840
 So can you maybe also tell us something about how we stand with the wholesale digital euro project?

1014
01:48:23,220 --> 01:48:35,380
 Well, what we say, we already have a digital wholesale, the CBDC, I mean, it's target, everything is, there's nothing tangible, there's no cash there, I mean.

1015
01:48:35,380 --> 01:48:44,120
 So in our view on wholesale, we already have a digital wholesale, central bank digital currency.

1016
01:48:44,120 --> 01:48:55,000
 Having said that, what currently the central bank is doing, or the ECB level, but with the cooperation of a lot of national central banks, is to explore new technology.

1017
01:48:55,000 --> 01:49:06,040
 So whether DLT solutions could add added value for certain use cases in different constructions are currently being explored together with market participants.

1018
01:49:06,040 --> 01:49:09,120
 So we are looking into that as well in parallel.

1019
01:49:09,120 --> 01:49:13,720
 Settling transactions on the DLT, yes, with the whole deal.

